-----------------------------------
Instructions for building TetrisOS:
-----------------------------------
Requirements:

Preferably a Linux Machine (WSL untested)
gcc
xorriso
syslinux (or a variant that is basically the same thing)

Building:

1. cd into the project folder
2. Add apps to initramfs_root/bin (need to be statically linked) (optional)
3. Add a command to launch that app in init.c (optional)
4. Run build.sh
5. The iso should be ready for use

Booting:

USB:
  Flash it using the dd command or use Ventoy

VM settings:
  Minimum 64MiB of RAM
  No disk
  x86_64 Architecture CPU
  For QEMU with VirtManager:
    Other Generic Linux 2024 (linux2024)
  For VMWare:
    Other Linux 6.x kernel 64bit
  For VirtualBox:
    Other Linux 64bit

Notes:
  If you dont like the bare metal feeling, choose the non-bare version
  All TetrisOS distributions will remain functional in apocalyptic, low RAM environments of as few as 64MiB.
